    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a concours-level 2002 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six. This unit exhibits a perfectly linear power band facilitated by its individual throttle bodies and a fully synchronized Double-VANOS system. The Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox offers short, positive throws, directing power to a Variable M Differential Lock. Crucially, the chassis has been future-proofed with a comprehensive rear subframe reinforcement and a documented rod bearing replacement using VAC coated bearings. The suspension utilizes OEM-plus Bilstein dampers, maintaining the factory roll center while sharpening turn-in response. The undercarriage is free of oxidation, and the engine bay is devoid of fluid weeping. This is a mechanically impeccable example of the ultimate driving machine, preserved for the discerning purist.",
      "price": 46500.0,
